## Development

- `just lint` runs every pre-commit check — the same entry point CI's `lint`
  job uses, so local and CI can't drift.
- Every change branches off `[[ protected_branch ]]`, squashes to one
  [Conventional Commit](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/), and rebase-merges
  back. The PR template's checklist covers doc ownership.
- Architecture decisions live in [`docs/adr/`](docs/adr/README.md) — create one
  with `just adr "Title"`; that README says when a change warrants an ADR.
